title: MMWR (CDC),  2008-2009 Flu Season Weekly mortality by large cities, USA, April 25 2009
name: MMWR (CDC),  2008-2009 Flu Season Weekly mortality by large cities, USA, April 25 2009
description: The point shapefile shows weekly mortality report for the flu season of 2008-2009 for selected cities with  100K or more population. Typically the flu season spans the winter months, according to NIH website the period starts in late October of a year and end the following year at the end of March. The weekly data collected by MMWR is a "voluntarily" submitted by selected cities (roughly 122) on the number of deaths reported due to all causes as well as number of deaths by various age groups and deaths due to pneumonia and influenza. The point shapefile has data on total number of deaths and deaths due to pneumonia and influenza for all the weeks starting in Oct 04, 2008 (week 40 of 2008) and ending on 25th April, 2009 (week 16 of 2009). During each week between zero to five cities on average do not "voluntarily" submit data, in that case the data is coded as zero. Also included in this dataset is a computed field for each week that shows the percent of deaths due to pneumonia/influenza.

author.source: CDC's Morbidity and Mortality Weekly Report Website
